Package: phontrast
Title: Contrast and Separation Metrics for Phonological Categories
Version: 2.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(c("Grant", "M."), "Berry", email = "berry.grant@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("ChatGPT", "Assistant", role = "ctb")
  )
Author: Grant M. Berry [aut, cre],
    ChatGPT Assistant [ctb]
Maintainer: Grant M. Berry <berry.grant@gmail.com>
Description: A unified toolkit for quantifying the separation and overlap
    between phonological categories (e.g., vowels, consonants) in arbitrary
    n-dimensional acoustic spaces such as formants, MFCCs, duration, or learned
    embeddings. The main entry point, phontrast(), computes and compares
    multiple contrast metrics in one call -- Jensen-Shannon divergence and
    distance, the Pillai-Bartlett trace, Bhattacharyya distance and affinity,
    Mahalanobis distance, and proportional overlap -- globally or by group, on a
    common separation-oriented scale. Includes bootstrap confidence intervals
    and utilities for preparing estimates for downstream modelling (GAMs,
    mixed-effects models). Formerly released as 'phonJSD'.
